title: Andrew Tate's home in Romania raided amid new allegations involving minors
content: Andrew Tate's house in Romania was raided by police following allegations of human trafficking and money laundering. The raid, conducted by Romania’s DIICOT, involved searches at four locations. Tate, his brother Tristan, and two Romanian women were previously arrested in 2022. Prosecutors have formally indicted all four, though they have denied the charges.

title: Andrew Tate, brother Tristan's residences raided by Romanian Police: What we know so far
content: Romanian police officers carried out fresh raids at the residences of controversial influencer Andrew Tate and his brother Tristan Tate in connection with the human trafficking and rape cases against Andrew Tate. One of the world’s best-known influencers, Andrew Tate is known for spouting his misogynist and divisive ideas to his millions of followers. The Tate brothers have been accused of having formed an organized criminal network in early 2021 in Romania and Britain. They have denied the charges and a trial date has not yet been set.

title: Ukraine’s drone strike targets Russia's Moscow in one of the largest attacks since February 2022
content: Ukraine launched a substantial drone offensive on Moscow, the most significant since the beginning of the conflict in February 2022. Russian air defences intercepted 11 drones in the Moscow area, with a total of 45 drones destroyed in multiple regions. Operations at Moscow’s major airports were disrupted temporarily.

title: Vessel off Yemen 'struck' by three projectiles: UK agency
content: Three projectiles hit a merchant vessel off Yemen's rebel-held port city of Hodeida on Wednesday, limiting the ship's ability to manoeuvre, British maritime security agency UKMTO said. It said there were no reports of casualties but "the vessel reports being not under command," meaning it was limited in its ability to manoeuvre, likely because of damage.
